(1+\sin t)^2 = 1^2 + 2\times 1 \times \sin t + \sin^2 t = 1 + 2\sin t + \sin^2 t.
\begin{align*} (1+\sin t)^2 + \cos^2 t &= \Bigl( 1 + 2\sin t + \sin^2 t\Bigr) + \cos^2 t\\ &= 1 + 2\sin t + \Bigl( \sin^2 t + \cos^2 t\Bigr)\\ &= 1 + 2\sin t + 1\\ & = 2 + 2\sin t\\ & = 2 (1 + \sin t). \end{align*}
